    "description": "PayU Digital Technologies is actively seeking a talented and motivated Financial Analyst to join our dynamic team in Vijayawada. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout PayU Digital Technologies:\nPayU Digital Technologies is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in GST\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with PayU Digital Technologies!",
